description: The Greek military has begun construction of new tents, despite opposition from migrants and locals.
title: Moria migrants and Greek islanders protest over new camp
title_page: Moria migrants and Greek islanders protest over new camp - BBC News
maintext: German Interior Minister Horst Seehofer said France and Germany would each accept between 100 and 150 of the children. The Netherlands has already pledged to accept 50 and Finland will take 11. Talks are ongoing with other states to take part, Mr Seehofer said.
